<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,431,1141]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,612,637]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
The specimens belong to the Simon collection and were probably exchanged with Kraepelin (Label “ex. typis). 
<bibRefCitation author="Muma" box="[494,700,647,672]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refString="Muma, M. H. (1970) A synoptic review oft he North American, Central American, and West Indian Solpugia. Florida Entomologist, 50, 115 - 123. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3493620" type="journal article" year="1970">Muma (1970: 16)</bibRefCitation>
noted that “the types in MNHN agree with Kraepelin's (1899) description in color and morphology but not with Roewer's (1932) statement of 4:4 ctenidia on the male. The female paratype (
<emphasis box="[352,439,721,744]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">ex typis</emphasis>
) in ZSM is not conspecific with the male, it is a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon)" authorityName="Simon" class="Arachnida" family="Eremobatidae" genus="Eremorhax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solifugae" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formidabilis">
<emphasis box="[1165,1436,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Eremorhax formidabilis</emphasis>
(Simon)
</taxonomicName>
”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Brookhart" box="[270,723,756,781]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refString="Brookhart, J. O. &amp; Brookhart, I. P. (2006) An annotated checklist of continental North American Solifugae with type depositories, abundance, and notes on their zoogeography. Journal of Arachnology, 34, 299 - 329. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / H 04 - 02.1" type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="p">Brookhart and Brookhart (2006, p. 308)</bibRefCitation>
stated that “male and female syntypes from Arizona, USA, no locality. No. 7297, Roewer No. 9129 (ZSM). These specimens agree with Kraepelin’s (1899) description and are therefore the types of the species. Muma’s (1970) type designation for 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1052,828,852]" class="Arachnida" family="Eremobatidae" genus="Eremoperna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solifugae" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[950,1052,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">E. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in MNHN are not the types”. But then 
<bibRefCitation author="Brookhart" box="[206,655,863,888]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refString="Brookhart, J. O. &amp; Brookhart, I. P. (2006) An annotated checklist of continental North American Solifugae with type depositories, abundance, and notes on their zoogeography. Journal of Arachnology, 34, 299 - 329. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / H 04 - 02.1" type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="p">Brookhart and Brookhart (2006, p. 303)</bibRefCitation>
also mention in the type material of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon 1879)" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1879" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Arachnida" family="Eremobatidae" genus="Eremocosta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solifugae" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formidabilis">
<emphasis box="[1069,1346,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Eremocosta formidabilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refString="Simon, E. (1879) Essai d'une classification des Galeodes, remarques synonymiques et description d'especes nouvelles ou mal connues. Annales de la Societ Entomologique de France, Series 5, Tome 9, 93 - 154." type="journal article" year="1879">Simon 1879</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
“ 
<emphasis box="[239,420,900,924]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Datames 
<taxonomicName box="[350,420,900,924]" class="Arachnida" family="Eremobatidae" genus="Eremoperna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Solifugae" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
: Male holotype and female allotype from Arizona, USA; No. 7297, Roewer No. 9129 (MNHN)”. Obviously, there is confusion about type determination and the ZMH specimens are best considered syntypes (and not paratypes as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Weidner" box="[534,694,972,997]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refString="Weidner, H. (1959) Die Entomologischen Sammlungen des Zoologischen Staatsinstituts und Zoologischen Museums Hamburg. I. Teil. Pararthropoda und Chelicerata I. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburger Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 57, 89 - 142." type="journal article" year="1959">Weidner 1959</bibRefCitation>
) until the specimens at the MNHN can be re-examined. It should be noted that 
<bibRefCitation author="Roewer" box="[315,538,1007,1032]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1934) Solifugae, Palpigradi. In: Dr. H. G. Bronns Klassen und Ordnungen des Tier-Reichs wissenschaftlich dargestellt in Wort und Bild. Funfter Band: Arthropoda. IV: Abeitlung: Arachnoidea und kleinere ihnen nahegestellte Arthropodengruppen. 3. Lieferung. Akademische Verlagsgesellschaft m. B. H., Leipzig, pp. 481 - 723." type="book chapter" year="1934">Roewer (1934:561)</bibRefCitation>
corrected a potential mistake by Kraepelin when he re-examined the Simon collection in Paris: the type specimen carries Kraepelin’s original label (“Typus”) and has an additional label by Simon that gives the type locality as ‘Arizona’ (not Arkansas).
</paragraph>
